quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  8,1,"They will ask thee about the spoils. Say, 'The spoils are God's and the Apostle's; fear God and settle it amongst yourselves; obey God and the Apostle if ye do believe"
  8,2,"Verily, the believers are those who, when God's name is mentioned, their hearts sink with fear; and when His signs are rehearsed to them they increase them in faith; and on their Lord do they rely"
  8,3,"who are steadfast in prayer, and of what we have bestowed upon them give in alms"
  8,4,"these are in truth believers; to them are degrees with their Lord, and forgiveness, and a generous provision"
  8,5,"As thy Lord caused thee to go forth from thy house with the truth, although a sect of the believers were averse therefrom"
  8,6,"They wrangled with thee about the truth after it was made plain, as though they were being driven on to death and looked thereon"
  8,7,"and when God promised you that one of the two troops should be yours, and ye would fain have had those who had no arms. God wished to prove the truth true by His words, and to cut off the hindermost parts of those who misbelieve"
  8,8,"to prove the truth true, and to make vain the vain, although the sinners are averse"
  8,9,"When ye asked for succour from your Lord, and He answered you, 'I will assist you with a thousand angels, with others in reserve"
  8,10,"God made it only glad tidings to quiet your hearts therewith; for victory is only from God! verily, God is mighty and wise"
  8,11,"When drowsiness covered you as a security from Him, and He sent down upon you from the heavens water to purify you withal, and to take away from you the plague of Satan, and to tie up your hearts and to make firm your footsteps"
  8,12,"When your Lord inspired the angels - 'Verily, I am with you; make ye firm then those who believe; I will cast dread into the hearts of those who misbelieve,- strike off their necks then, and strike off from them every finger tip"
  8,13,"That is, because they went into opposition against God and His Apostle; for he who goes into opposition against God and His Apostle - verily, God is keen to punish"
  8,14,"There, taste it! since for the misbelievers is the torment of the Fire"
  8,15,"O ye who believe! when ye meet those who misbelieve in swarms, turn not to them your hinder parts"
  8,16,"for he who turns to them that day his hinder parts, save turning to fight or rallying to a troop, brings down upon himself wrath from God, and his resort is hell, and an ill journey shall it be"
  8,17,"Ye did not slay them, but it was God who slew them; nor didst thou shoot when thou didst shoot, but God did shoot, to try the believers from Himself with a goodly trial; verily, God both hears and knows"
  8,18,"There! verily, God weakens the stratagem of the misbelievers"
  8,19,"If ye wish the matter to be decided, a decision has now come to you; but if ye desist, it is better for you; and if ye turn back we will turn too, and your troop shall avail nothing, great in number though it be, since God is with the believers"
  8,20,"O ye who believe! obey God and His Apostle, and turn not from Him while ye hear"
  8,21,"and be not like those who say, 'We hear,' and yet they hear not"